quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  17,109,"And they fall upon their faces weeping, and it [i.e., the Qur’ān] increases them in humble submission."
  17,110,"Say, "
  17,111,"And say, "
  18,76,"[Moses] said, "
  18,77,"So they set out, until when they came to the people of a town, they asked its people for food, but they refused to offer them hospitality. And they found therein a wall about to collapse, so he [i.e., al-Khiḍr] restored it. [Moses] said, "
  18,78,"[Al-Khiḍr] said, "
  19,37,"Then the factions differed [concerning Jesus] from among them, so woe to those who disbelieved - from the scene of a tremendous Day."
  19,38,"How [clearly] they will hear and see the Day they come to Us, but the wrongdoers today are in clear error."
  19,39,"And warn them, [O Muḥammad], of the Day of Regret, when the matter will be concluded;{1} and [yet], they are in [a state of] heedlessness, and they do not believe.",footnotes:1:i.e., "judged" or "accomplished."
  20,19,"[Allāh] said, "
  20,20,"So he threw it down, and thereupon it was a snake, moving swiftly."
  20,21,"[Allāh] said, "